<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Pseudo element selector</title>
    <style>
        h1::first-letter{
            color: rgb(220, 163, 8);
        }
        p::after{
            content: 'Bye Jspiders!';
        }
        p::before{
            content: 'Bye Jspiders!';
        }
        p::selection{
            background-color: aqua;
            color: blueviolet;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>JSpiders</h1>
    <p>Hello Jspiders!</p>
    <p>Lorem, ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Dolorem animi fugiat quam labore! Dicta iure, odio blanditiis qui quis dolorum ex! Voluptate aspernatur quod minima repelle.
    Cupiditate in, molestiae omnis expedita fuga vero a recusandae molestias officiis natus temporibus eius repellat maxime quidem tenetur explicabo alias eaque ducimus
    porro aspernatur suscipit nobis ipsam animi provident quidem ducimus odit quaerat deleniti soluta ab, earum id deserunt illum sint sequi autem rem magnam amet harum libero? Quibusdam?
   </p>
</body>
</html>
<!--By using pseudo element selctor we can apply css styles for specific part of html elements.
it is represented by using '::'-->
